title: A generic greedy algorithm, partially-ordered graphs and NP-completeness.
abstract: Let π be any fixed polynomial-time testable, non-trivial, hereditary property of graphs. Suppose that the vertices of a graph G are not necessarily linearly ordered but partially ordered, where we think of this partial order as a collection of (possibly exponentially many) linear orders in the natural way. We prove that the problem of deciding whether a lexicographically first maximal subgraph of G satisfying π, with respect to one of these linear orders, contains a specified vertex is NP-complete
